name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
On May 4, a man was killed with a knife on the K435 train from Wuchang to Huizhou. The murderer was arrested on the spot by the train police. The deceased and the murderer did not know each other.
The mother of the deceased questioned why an 18 cm long knife could be brought on the high-speed train.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
Recently, a tourist uploaded a video saying that someone buried triangular nails in the sand in an off-road desert scenic spot in Tongliao, Inner Mongolia, causing the tires of many tourists' cars to be punctured.
After the person concerned called the police, the police said it was difficult to manage. After negotiations, the scenic spot said that the ticket would be free next time.
At present, the local response has set up a joint investigation team to conduct an investigation.

On May 8, the Shanxi Luliangshan Revolutionary Museum issued an alternative closure notice, stating that the museum director Gao was insulted and pushed down by the district head Zhang while doing business at the district government, and was injured. His current state is very unstable, so he cannot open the museum normally. We apologize to everyone.
